 to comedy and charity, along with his publicized personal life made him a global figure in pop culture over an eight-decade career. He professionally debuted in 1946 as part of the famous Martin and Lewis with singer Dean Martin and performed with him until 1956, then went solo after the split. \nBy becoming the highest grossing movie star and innovative filmmaker, he helped to develop and popularize \"video assist\", the closed-circuit apparatus enabling film directors to see what had been shot without waiting for developed film footage. In addition to starring in sixty films, Lewis directed 13 movies. He was also national chairman of the Muscular Dystrophy Association (MDA) and host of The Jerry Lewis Telethon each Labor Day weekend for many years.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T11:57:58.520215+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2377, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerry_Lewis"}], "uuid": "3678ba4e-743e-4e75-bc90-49b090beb448", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "21805", "external_references": [{"id": 10185, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q294927"}, {"id": 10186, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "98006568"}, {"id": 10187, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n50053444"}, {"id": 10188, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n50053444"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:30:25.990078+10:00"}, {"id": 27108, "name": "ATP", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2788625, "title": "Look up and laugh", "work_id": 85185, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T20:07:57.563216+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "b8be66ef-f027-4013-a649-18